The long circulatory half-life of albumin facilitated by the interaction with 
the cellular recycling neonatal Fc receptor (FcRn) is utilized for drug 
half-life extension. FcRn engagement effects following covalent attachment of 
cargo to cysteine 34, however, have not been investigated. Poly(ethylene glycol) 
polymers were used to study the influence of cargo molecular weight on human 
